 you can use custom HttpServletRequestWrapper to override getMethod() 

```java
public class ChangeHttpMethodFilter extends OncePerRequestFilter {

    public class ChangeHttpMethodHttpServletRequestWrapper extends HttpServletRequestWrapper {
        public ChangeHttpMethodHttpServletRequestWrapper(HttpServletRequest request) {
            super(request);
        }

        @Override
        public String getMethod() {
            HttpMethod method = HttpMethod.resolve(this.getRequest().getParameter(&quot;method&quot;));
            return method == null ? super.getMethod() : method.name();
        }
    }

    @Override
    protected void doFilterInternal(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response, FilterChain chain) throws ServletException, IOException {
        HttpServletRequest changeHttpMethodRequest = new ChangeHttpMethodHttpServletRequestWrapper(request);
        chain.doFilter(changeHttpMethodRequest, response);
    }
}
```

